FBIS3-45215 "drchi010op_94002" FBIS-CHI-94-010 Document Type:Daily Report 14 Jan 1994 REGIONAL AFFAIRS East Region Jiangxi Sets Up 2,000 Family Planning `Schools' OW1301020394 Beijing XINHUA in English 0151 GMT 13 Jan 94 OW1301020394 Beijing XINHUA Language: English Article Type:BFN [Text] Nanchang, January 13 (XINHUA) -- East China's Jiangxi Province is spreading family planning knowledge through spare time schools. Zhu Jufang, deputy director of Jiangxi Provincial Family Planning Commission, said that in 1,782 townships, towns and plants in the province, there are now 2,027 family planning schools with 10,500 teachers. She said that most of the schools are equipped with color TV's, tape recorders and other modern teaching facilities. The schools give classes to and provide textbooks for people according to sex, age, occupation and marital status. Up to now, about 2.2 million people have received instruction in the schools. The family-planning education effectively raised people's understanding of family planning policies and more and more people have begun to abandon traditional birth concepts.
